This article discusses an executive order issued by President Donald Trump on February 9, 2017. The order aims to reduce crime and restore public safety in communities across the United States. It states that the executive branch will focus on enforcing the law and developing policies to address illegal immigration, drug trafficking, and violent crime. The Attorney General is directed to establish a Task Force on Crime Reduction and Public Safety, which will exchange information and ideas, develop strategies, identify deficiencies in existing laws, propose new legislation, evaluate crime-related data, and submit reports to the President. The order also includes general provisions that clarify its implementation and state that it does not create any enforceable rights or benefits.